cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper deals with social media data harvesting and visualization, specifically utilizing Twitter graphs related to topics of suicidality. The paper discusses the topological features of the graphs, clustering coefficients, and centrality measures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper utilizes NodeXL for data analysis. The paper also discusses sentiment analysis, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper deals with social issues related to suicidality, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
